  "narrative": "DRIVER\nUSD leads D1 CSM at 100 but is fading hard on H4 at 44, a 56-point divergence that is the single most important signal in this session, while CHF accelerates to H4 100 versus D1 33 and AUD surges to H4 70 versus D1 31, confirming a sharp intraday rotation out of USD into CHF and commodity currencies against a Risk-Off High regime backdrop with copper up 1.36% and S&P 500 up 0.37% pulling risk proxies higher. USDCHF is the cleanest expression of the USD fade paired with CHF acceleration, while AUDUSD and AUDCHF capture the AUD surge with the commodity bid reinforcing it.\n\nMOMENTUM\nGaining: None\nFading: None\n\nWATCH\nUS 10Y yield at 4.558 down 0.61% deepening steepens the curve against 2Y at 3.585 rising, USDJPY breaks lower if the long-end extends its drop confirming USD bearish momentum.\nWTI Oil extending above 96.6 directly pressures USDCAD lower as CAD H4 CSM sits at 0 and any energy-driven CAD bid accelerates the pair's downside.\nGold holding below 4521 on renewed risk appetite triggers XAUUSD selling continuation if S&P 500 extends above 7473.",
